   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON THIRTEEN THE DANGER AND LOSS</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF NOT USING OUR GIFT Scripture Reading: Matt 24:48-51; 25:24-31 OUTLINE The danger: Beating our fellow slaves mistreating fellow believers 24:49a.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Eating and drinking with the drunken keeping company with people who are drunken with worldly things 24:49b.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Hiding our gift in the earth 25:25: Being passive, not active, for the Lord's service.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Merely keeping the Lord's gift, neither losing it nor gaining a profit by using it.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The loss: To be cut off from the Lord at His coming back to be separated from the Lord in His coming glory 24:51: To be chastened dispensationally.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In weeping and gnashing of teeth.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To lose our gift 25:28-29.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To be cast out into the darkness outside of the Lord's coming glory 25:30; 8:12.</S>
   </TEXT>
